<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1502] TSimpleServer::serve(): Do not print out error message if server was stopped.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1502</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the following error message is displayed upon calling TSimpleServer::stop():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &quot;TServerTransport died on accept: TTransportException: Interrupted&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The message originates from TSimpleServer::serve(). This message should not be displayed if the server came to a clean stop. I&apos;ve provided a patch to fix this. This small fix is taken from the other servers, such as TThreadedServer, which do not have this issue. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
